# Playground runtime assets (public/pgrt/) are DERIVED by `make playground-assets`
# but COMMITTED: the Vercel Node build has no Go toolchain to regenerate the wasm,
# so /try ships the built assets directly. Regenerate and recommit after any
# kernel or corpus change (a stale wasm/snapshot would serve outdated verdicts).

# EXCEPTION: the Z3 browser assets ARE regenerable in a Node build — they come
# from the z3-solver dependency, which Vercel installs. scripts/gen-z3-assets.mjs
# reproduces them at predev/prebuild time, so they are gitignored rather than
# committing 32MB of derivable wasm. (z3-worker.js is authored, not generated.)
/public/pgrt/z3/z3-built.js
/public/pgrt/z3/z3-built.wasm
/public/pgrt/z3/z3-solver.js
